GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 441
Senate Finance Committee Substitute Adopted 6/19/25
Short Title: Shrimp Trawling Transition Program/Fees. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 20, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ESTABLISH THE SHRIMP TRAWL TRANSITION PROGRAM TO PROVIDE
3 TEMPORARY TRANSITION PAYMENTS TO HOLDERS OF COMMERCIAL FISHING
4 LICENSES WHO HAD REPORTED SALES OF SHRIMP CAUGHT WITH A TRAWL
5 NET BETWEEN JANUARY 1, 2023, AND JUNE 30, 2025, AND TO INCREASE
6 COASTAL FISHING LICENSE FEES.
7 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
8
9 SHRIMP TRAWL TRANSITION PAYMENT PROGRAM
10 SECTION 1.(a) Shrimp Trawl Transition Program. – The Shrimp Trawl Transition
11 Program (Program) is established within the Department of Environmental Quality's Division of
12 Marine Fisheries (Division). Funding for the Program shall come from the North Carolina
13 Commercial Fishing Resource Fund and the North Carolina Marine Resources Fund. The
14 Program shall be used to provide annual transition payments to eligible holders of commercial
15 fishing licenses with verifiable landings of shrimp between January 1, 2023, and June 30, 2025.
16 The Program shall expire October 1, 2028. To be eligible for a transition payment, a person must
17 satisfy all of the following criteria:
18 (1) The person held a Standard Commercial Fishing License or a Retired Standard
19 Commercial Fishing License at any time between January 1, 2023, and June
20 30, 2025.
21 (2) The person reported on trip tickets submitted to the Division of Marine
22 Fisheries the sale of brown shrimp, pink shrimp, or white shrimp caught with
23 a trawl net between January 1, 2023, and June 30, 2025.
24 SECTION 1.(b) Retained Eligibility. – A person who holds a Standard Commercial
25 Fishing License or a Retired Standard Commercial Fishing License who harvests shrimp using
26 legal commercial gear within the area described in G.S. 113-187(d)(3a) or using any gear,
27 including trawl nets, outside of the area described in G.S. 113-187(d)(3a), may still be eligible
28 for a transition payment from the Program, provided the person otherwise meets the criteria in
29 subsection (a) of this section.
30 SECTION 1.(c) Documentation. – A person seeking a transition payment pursuant
31 to the Program shall submit documentation verifying that the person meets the criteria in
32 subsection (a) of this section, including copies of all trip tickets submitted for brown shrimp, pink
33 shrimp, or white shrimp caught with a trawl net between January 1, 2023, and June 30, 2025, to
34 the Division no later than December 1, 2025.
35 SECTION 1.(d) Program Payment Criteria. – The Division shall administer the
36 Program in accordance with the following criteria:
*H441-v-2*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The annual transition payment amount awarded to a Program applicant shall
2 be set at the sum of (i) the value of the eligible shrimp trip tickets submitted
3 by the applicant under subsection (a) of this section and (ii) one hundred
4 eighty dollars ($180.00). For applicants that hold more than one Standard
5 Commercial Fishing License or Retired Standard Commercial Fishing
6 License, the annual transition payment amount awarded shall be set at the sum
7 of (i) the value of the eligible shrimp trip tickets associated with the license
8 with the highest reported shrimp landings and (ii) one hundred eighty dollars
9 ($180.00).
10 (2) The Division shall gather all trip ticket information from Program applicants
11 no later than December 1, 2025. If the total of Program payments calculated
12 and verified by the Division for each Program applicant is greater than the
13 funds available for the Program in the North Carolina Commercial Fishing
14 Resource Fund and the North Carolina Marine Resources Fund, then the
15 Division shall provide to each eligible applicant a portion of the Program
16 payments by allocating the funds available in proportion to the Program
17 payments documented by each applicant.
18 SECTION 1.(e) Reporting. – The Department shall submit a report to the Joint
19 Legislative Oversight Committee on Agriculture and Natural and Economic Resources and the
20 Fiscal Research Division no later than October 1, 2025, and annually thereafter until all funds
21 are expended or the Program expires containing, at a minimum, all of the following data:
22 (1) The number of Program applicants.
23 (2) The number and amount of transition payments awarded.
24 (3) The total amount of funding available to the Program, the total amount
25 encumbered, and the total amount disbursed to date.
26 SECTION 1.(f) Effective Date and Expiration. – If House Bill 442, 2025 Regular
27 Session, becomes law, then this section is effective when it becomes law and expires October 1,
28 2028.
29
30 INCREASE COASTAL FISHING LICENSE FEES
