32 SECTION 2.(l) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the North
33 Carolina Commercial Fishing Resource Fund, established in G.S. 113-173.1, and the North
34 Carolina Marine Resources Fund, established in G.S. 113-175.1, may be used to provide Shrimp
35 Trawl Transition Program payments to eligible applicants as set forth in Section 1 of this act.
36 SECTION 2.(m) If House Bill 442, 2025 Regular Session, becomes law, then this
37 section becomes effective July 1, 2025, applies to licenses issued on or after that date, and expires
38 June 30, 2028.
